# Summary

<div class="block excerpt">

![Monotonic Sequence Theorem](/img/graphs/calculus/monotonic-sequence-theorem.png)

A **sequence** is a list of numbers written in a definite order: $$ \inflate{a}{n}, \ldots $$ Sequences are also denoted 
$\{a_n\}$ and $\{a_n\}_{n=1}^{\infty}$. A **series** is the sequence generated by the partial sums of a sequence. That is, 
if we try to add the terms of an infinite sequence $\{a_n\}_{n=1}^{\infty}$ we get an expression of the form 
$$ \inflate[+]{a}{n} + \cdots $$ and is denoted by the symbols $$ \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} a_n \text{ or } \sum a_n. $$

